	"title": "Les nombres et l'heure — Numbers, days & time",
	"objective": "Count, ask and tell the time, and name the days of the week (A1: can handle numbers, quantities and time).",
	"bridge": {
		"title": "Bridge from Hindi / English: telling time with « il est … heures »",
		"body": "French tells the time impersonally: **Il est trois heures** = “It is three o’clock” (literally “It is three hours”). English uses “o’clock”; Hindi uses तीन बजे (teen baje). Numbers 1–16 are unique words to memorise (like Hindi एक, दो, तीन…), then they become regular. Don’t forget the silent letters: **deux** sounds like /dø/ (the x is silent)."
	},
